# BTCPay Server â€“ Spanish Translation  
Full Spanish translation file for BTCPay Server.

This repository contains the file "Espanol.json", which includes a complete Spanish translation that can be imported directly into any BTCPay Server instance using the built-in translation system.

---

# ðŸ‡¬ðŸ‡§ Instructions â€“ How to Install the Spanish Translation for BTCPay Server

BTCPay Server does not use external JSON files directly. Instead, translations must be added as internal dictionaries inside the BTCPay interface.

Below are the correct installation steps.

---

## Add the Translation Using the BTCPay Server Interface (UI) â€” Recommended Method

Steps:

1. Log in to your BTCPay Server.  
2. Navigate to: Server Settings â†’ Translations  
3. Click "Create" to create a new translation dictionary.  
4. When the system asks for the dictionary name, you may enter any of the following:

Spanish  
Espanol  
es  
es-ES  

5. Open the file from this repository: Espanol.json  
6. Copy the ENTIRE content of the file exactly as it is.  
7. Paste everything into the translation editor (the large text box inside BTCPay).  
8. Click "Save".  
9. Click "Select" to activate the translation.  
10. Reload the BTCPay interface.

Your BTCPay Server will now display the full Spanish translation.

---

## Optional: Manual Dictionary Creation (Without Using the File)

Steps:

1. Go to Server Settings â†’ Translations.  
2. Click "Create".  
3. Use any dictionary name such as:

Spanish  
Espanol  
es  
es-ES  

4. Manually translate each entry shown on the left into Spanish on the right.  
5. Click "Save".  
6. Click "Select" to activate.

---

